sd=Customer Campaign Execution	Execute a customer campaign (version) and track and respond to impact	A bank implements a targeted cross-sell campaign in the customer servicing center to generate additional sales	Handle the deployment, execution and on-going refinement of a customer campaign. This includes many types of proactive customer campaigns such as up-sell, cross-sell and customer retention. The campaign execution process performs the initial selection and confirmation of candidate customers and includes providing critical feedback on the impact of the campaign to the design unit to support re-calibration and refinement of the specification based on practical experience
sdpath=customer-campaign-execution
crpath=customer-campaign-procedure
crr=Customer Campaign Procedure Instance
mcr=Customer Campaign Procedure
bqs=CandidateSelection Execution Analysis
CONFIG
CustomerCampaignProcedure	initiate	Initiate customer campaign processing		initiateCustomerCampaignProcedure		#desc
CustomerCampaignProcedure	update	Update details of an active customer campaign		updateCustomerCampaignProcedure		#desc
CustomerCampaignProcedure	control	Control the execution of a customer campaign (e.g. suspend)		controlCustomerCampaignProcedure		#desc
CustomerCampaignProcedure	exchange	Accept, reject, etc. a customer campaign procedure		exchangeCustomerCampaignProcedure		#desc
CustomerCampaignProcedure	execute	Execute an automated action against an active customer campaign (e.g. order inventory)		executeCustomerCampaignProcedure		#desc
CustomerCampaignProcedure	request	Request manual intervention in a campaign (e.g. add candidate to list)		requestCustomerCampaignProcedure		#desc
CustomerCampaignProcedure	retrieve	Retrieve details about an active customer campaign		retrieveCustomerCampaignProcedure		#desc
